title: Grateful Dead Live at Sam Boyd Silver Bowl, U.N.L.V. on 1993-05-16
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi CR-7A) > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.8 MHz) >KORG AudioGate 4 > Samplitude Pro X3 Suite > FLAC/24
description:
Set 1

Touch Of Grey, Walkin' Blues, Althea, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Row Jimmy, Cassidy

Set 2

Samson & Delilah, Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower-> Looks Like Rain-> Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Jam-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> Throwing Stones-> Turn On Your Love Light, E: Brokedown Palace

Sting opened

reviews.review_text:
SACK TWISTING BASS IN SET 2 / GREAT SHORT SET 1 This is an apparently pretty famous show, and apparently pretty well liked, so I checked it out. I also was blessed to witness 6 shows that year as a 19 yr old college kid, but they were all East Coast, so I was not at this Vegas run.

But if they're looking for a review to see whether or not it's worth listening to or downloading I would say yes! And if you're wondering what the highlights are, i'll say:

Masterpiece-> to end of set is the highlight with tge CASSIDY JAM getting extra notice

Set 2
Samson: bass suddenly gets LOUD during (yay)
Slipknot: mini trainwreck
Franklins: great jamming
LLR - great solos
Terrapin- NICE 3 min jam at end
Drums- cut short?
Space - WTF??? I WOULD HAVE LOST MY SHIT
Other One - WOW
Wharf Rat- SHRED/INSANE peak / great , HARD jamning on guitars by bob and jerry at end... cool interplay then excellent build up where they throw in a chord ive not heard... GREAT VERSION
Throwin Stones -more great in-verse Jamming during ENTIRE song and again builds to.an even.MORE furious peak with tumbling bass lines from high cliffs, perfect eagle soar solos, crashing and splashing cymbals literally into the ending.  Croad ROARS the lyrics, short unusual jam moment, BIG ending, hilarious vocal flub!!  This version has it all.
Lovelight->  more FUN hard distorted rhythm , interestingly PACED buildup with more snappy punching bag grinding bass guitar twist and turns.  FUN.  Jerry adds a really great little guitar part towards the end that I never heard him do elsewhere!  Def noticeable.

Anyways... awesome 5 star buildup with the occasional eyebrow raise moment. 

Encore: They dont play this and it "sucks" so enjoy another sweer one here


 
Best sounding SBD source too!!
Sound 5 stars
Playing 4.5
4.75 stars overall
 (Rounds to 5)
!!!
